Detailed Description

cvmx_sriomaint::_sec_dev_id

Secondary 8 and 16 bit device IDs. This register defines the secondary 8 and 16 bit device IDs used for large and small transport. The corresponding secondary ID must be written before the ID is enabled in the SRIOMAINT()_SEC_DEV_CTRL register. The primary set of device IDs are located in SRIOMAINT()_PRI_DEV_ID register. The secondary IDs should not be written to the same values as the corresponding primary IDs.
